---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Shop" description="Sportlad merch — print-on-demand, zero stock held. Starter range live now, more once the community's made it its own.">
  <h1 style="margin-top: 32px;">Shop</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--muted); max-width: 60ch;">
    Print-on-demand, so nothing's held in stock and nothing sits here unsold. A small starter range is live —
    it won't be pushed hard until the community's produced its own in-jokes and catchphrases worth printing.
  </p>

  <div class="section-head"><h2>Starter Range</h2></div>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="tag">Live</span>
      <h3>Sportlad Logo Cap</h3>
      <p>Embroidered wordmark, adjustable strap.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="tag">Live</span>
      <h3>Sportlad Logo Hoodie</h3>
      <p>Heavyweight, front wordmark print.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="tag">Live</span>
      <h3>Sportlad Logo Tee</h3>
      <p>Classic fit, chest print.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.85rem;">
    Placeholder listing — connect a POD provider (Printful or Printify, both integrate cleanly here) and swap in real product
    images/pricing before this goes live for real orders. This site already has a Shopify connector available if you'd
    rather run the storefront through Shopify directly instead of a custom checkout.
  </p>
</Layout>
